1st 

🔹 1. Initialize Repository
mkdir data-science-project
cd data-science-project
git init
✔ Explanation:
mkdir → creates folder
cd → enters folder
git init → starts Git tracking
👉 Now your project is under version control

🔹 2. Connect GitHub (FIX NEEDED)
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR-USERNAME/data-science-project.git
git remote -v
✔ Explanation:
origin = name of remote repo
URL is required (you missed it earlier)
git remote -v → checks connection

🔹 3. Create program1.py (Even/Odd)
touch program1.py
nano program1.py
👉 Add code:
num = int(input("Enter number: "))
if num % 2 == 0:
   print("Even")
else:
   print("Odd")
✔ Explanation:
touch → creates file
nano → opens editor (Linux)

🔹 4. Commit & Push
git add .
git commit -m "Added program1"
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
✔ Explanation:
git add . → stage all files
commit → save snapshot
push → upload to GitHub

🔹 5. Create Branch
git checkout -b GIT-EXAM
✔ Explanation:
Creates a new branch (separate workspace)

🔹 6. Create program2.py (Reverse String)
touch program2.py
nano program2.py
👉 Add code:
text = input("Enter string: ")
print(text[::-1])

🔹 7. Commit & Push Branch
git add .
git commit -m "Added program2"
git push -u origin GIT-EXAM
git diff main GIT-EXAM
